summary: The document is a forensic analysis report from the ABC Forensic Services Laboratory regarding latent print examination and comparison for case number B2022-16584. Several items were processed for latent prints, and a print on a metal box was identified as belonging to Ryan Gillespie. Other prints were either not found or deemed insufficient for comparison.
conclusion: A latent fingerprint on a metal box was identified as belonging to Ryan Gillespie, while other prints were insufficient for comparison or not found.

description: Black metal box with latch containing insulated material and cardboard
Latent fingerprint of value found on cardboard, identified as Ryan Gillespie's right thumb
Black Glock 17 pistol, 9x19 mm caliber with obliterated serial number and unloaded magazine
Latent impressions found but insufficient for comparison
Seven stray bronze and silver 9mm unfired cartridges with Luger headstamp
Known fingerprint standards of Gerald Gillespie
Used for comparison and excluded as source of latent print
